The Grinnell College newspaper began in 1871 as the iOWA COLLEGE NEWSLETTER
and later incorporated the PULSE, a competing college publication, to for-m a paper called
THE UNIT. In the early 1890’s, that paper changed its name to the SCARLET & BLACK.
Long noted as ”the oldest college newspaper West or the Mississippi," the 5&3 begins
its 194th semester or publication with portraits or J. n. Grinnell and Horace bradley in
its bag.
bradley told Grinnell to go West and thus joined a byword in American history. This
