TWO llIl SYSTEMS SEEN
BY DAVE RENAUD
S E: B Staff Writer
Contrary to popular belief,
The resident advisor (RA) system at Grinnell College is not
one system, but two. The two
systems are run by two different people, Alice Low. dean
in women, and Eugene Thompson, dean of men, with two diff
recent ideas on what the system
is supposed to do.
A poster which was sent out
for recruitment purposes to colleges and universities in various
parts of the country reads. in
part:
“Responsibilities i n c l u d e
counseling or approximately
100 students, with special
emphasis on advisory lresiimen, and generally contributing tn the quality and social and academic life in the
residence calls in cooperation
with elected studentvgovem.
meat officers, house councils,
Ind the Dean of Men Ind
Dean of Women."
The poster goes on to say that
“In addition" the resident advisors can be involved in academic or demonstration activities of the college commentary.
INTERPRETATION OF
DUTIES
John partial, former RA for
