GERMAN RADICAL
UNIVERSITIES
BERLIN (CPS)—The paradox
of being a “radical Student" is
that you have to belong to a
university, which almost auto.
basically makes you un-radical.
’At the same time, the united‘u
city is considered the ideal
place to “basically " others.
This paradox has been especially nursing in Germany,
whose public is still going
through a thank-God-we’re-notextremist—any-more stage. Most
people are scared to death of
radicalism on the right or left,
